Defence Correspondent
Published at 12:01AM, March 28 2013
The Government will face a huge hidden bill for cleaning up the legacy of decades of British military activity in Germany, Labour politicians have claimed.
Kevan Jones, Shadow Defence Minister, said that the Government had failed to assess costs of tens of millions of pounds for the environmental clean-up at ranges and training areas covering 30,000 hectares of Germany’s Rhine region. The areas have endured decades of tank, artillery and small arms barrages, as well as potential environmental damage caused by heavy vehicles, fuel leaks and other hazardous substances.
